12 (ix) a public or nonpublic school.
13 (b) "Vulnerable person" means:
14 (i) a child; or
15 (ii) a vulnerable adult as provided in 52-3-803(11)(b); or
16 (iii) an incapacitated person as provided in 72-5-101.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 and 2] are intended to be codified
19 as an integral part of Title 46, chapter 18, part 2, and the provisions of Title 46, chapter 18, part 2, apply to
20 [sections 1 and 2].
